item.title: Can people help my please?
item.dc:creator: @Epic_Ancient Epic Ancient
item.description:
@Epic_Ancient wrote:

To clarify:

Spelling doesn’t matter through age; it’s how the person types.
If they go fast, they might make mistakes.
Common mistakes are from speed and/or carelessness.

If I see a mistake, I usually backspace it out and retype it. But it’s a force of habit.
I spell/type well because I have been doing it for years. People don’t spell/type well because they either don’t want to, don’t care, or are too lazy to do anything about it.

Spelling might matter, but as long as we get the point, who cares? Spelling helps you understand it BETTER, 'tis all.

~I r 17, and, as you saw before, younger people type well. It’s a matter of habit tbh.
